    [35mevent[39m: "faction.tick"
    [35mpayload[39m: {
      "action": "Withdraw Warden Guardpost garrison from the canal approach chokepoint to Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier and consolidate all forces at Tower Bridge Concourse. Reinforce the tariff checkpoint with additional polearm guards and establish a fortified barricade to control access. Issue a formal Warden decree declaring that all commercial traffic must still pass through Tower Bridge Concourse for inspection, regardless of Signal-House or Council charters, and threaten cargo confiscation for non-compliance.",
      "outcome": "The Wardens pull back from their exposed canal approach position overnight, abandoning the chokepoint that had been strangling gondola traffic to the Lantern-Lit Gondola Pier. The withdrawal is orderly but humiliating — the Signal-House Families' agents document the retreat and spread word that the Wardens have been \"routed.\" At Tower Bridge Concourse, the consolidated garrison fortifies the checkpoint with timber barricades and additional crossbow positions. The Warden decree is posted at dawn, but its authority is immediately challenged: the Shrine Auditors' Council reiterates that all Warden permits are annulled, and the Signal-House Families announce that their \"doubly authenticated\" gondolas will bypass Tower Bridge entirely under liturgical protection. Several merchants who had quietly supported the Wardens' tariff system — benefiting from river-tax exemptions — now waver, uncertain whether the Wardens can hold even their remaining position. The consolidation saves the garrison from total collapse, but the Wardens have lost the initiative. They are now besieged in their own checkpoint, surrounded by hostile jurisdictions and hemorrhaging credibility.",
      "targetLocation": "Tower Bridge Concourse",
