      "action": "Deploy shrine auditors trained in liturgical cryptography to the Silent Spire to perform a consecration ritual, using encoded hymns designed to counter the Keepers' acoustic jamming and assert liturgical jurisdiction over the Spire's transmission mechanisms.",
      "outcome": "The shrine auditors approach the Silent Spire at dawn, chanting consecrated frequencies calibrated to penetrate the Keepers' acoustic jamming field. The ritual partially succeeds — the auditors establish a consecrated perimeter around the Spire's outer ring, claiming liturgical jurisdiction over the exterior transmission arrays. However, the Keepers' sealed mechanism vault and the core pronouncement chamber remain impenetrable; the \"unspoken tongue\" protocols reject the auditors' cryptographic hymns. The Council now holds contested sacred ground around the Spire, but the Keepers retreat deeper into the inner sanctum, activating secondary jamming that disrupts the auditors' signal logs. A tense standoff emerges: the Council controls the outer consecrated ring, the Keepers hold the vaulted core, and neither can claim full jurisdiction. The auditors establish a temporary liturgical checkpoint at the Spire's threshold, demanding any who enter submit to Council audit — a direct challenge to the Keepers' isolationist doctrine.",
      "targetLocation": "The Silent Spire",
      "tagChangeCount": 3,
      "chronicleEntryId": "4fe95e47-44b3-454d-a49e-611ce2c81506"
    }
