      "outcome": "The Lacquer Seal Verification Authority secures the Seal Verification Chamber's full consecrated archive — including the master authentication protocols, original lacquer formulae, and consecration records that gave the Shrine Auditors' Council jurisdiction over message authentication. The artificers spirit the materials back to the Resin Mixing Chamber under cover of routine operations. When the Council's remaining clerks discover the extraction days later, the Authority has already copied and catalogued everything. The Council faces a fait accompli: their liturgical authority over seal verification has been hollowed out while they were focused on the Silent Spire. The Authority now holds the technical foundation for a monopoly.",
      "targetLocation": "Resin Mixing Chamber",
